node.text:
You have never tried an #omelet this tasty!

INGREDIENTS
Red bell pepper
Yellow bell pepper
6 eggs
50g parmesan
Chives
Garlic
Thyme
Extra virgin olive oil
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
Add minced garlic and oil to a pan. Sprinkle over dried thyme. Cut the peppers, add to the pan, and cook. Then add chives
Pour 6 eggs into a bowl, add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly
Add the pepper mixture to the bowl with the egg and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a pan and cook on both sides to get an omelet.

node.text:
This #chocolatepudding is so creamy and irresistible!

INGREDIENTS
1l (4 cups) milk
2 egg yolks
1 cup flour
1 cup sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 tbsp butter
1 tsp vanilla sugar
1/2 cup chocolate
240ml (1 cup) water
Biscuits
 
METHOD
Into the pan add egg yolks, flour, cocoa powder, sugar, and milk, cook on low heat until thick. Add in butter, chocolate, and vanilla extract. Turn off the heat and pour in water.
Layout biscuits on the bottom of each plate. Cover them with prepared chocolate mixture, and repeat it again. Refrigerate for 1 hour, sprinkle with more chocolate chips.

node.text:
Just eggs, veggies and a muffin pan to make an incredible dinner! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
Butter
1 onion
Garlic
Carrots
Red pepper
Leeks
4 eggs
80ml (1/3 cup) milk
Parmesan
Salt
Black pepper
Extra virgin olive oil
 
METHOD
Melt the butter in a frying pan. Then add grated garlic, carrot, onion, red pepper, leek, salt, pepper, and mix. Put in a bowl once cooked.
Mix the eggs and milk in a bowl, add salt and pepper, then add the cooked vegetables and mix well.
Brush some oil over the muffin tray then pour in the egg mixture. Cook for 15 minutes at 200ºC (392ºF).

This idea is so cute, perfect to surprise everyone with a few basic ingredients! 

INGREDIENTS
320g (2.5 cups) flour
3 tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp salt
7g dry yeast
190ml (3/4 cup) warm milk
1 egg
1 egg yolk
3 tbsp soft butter
Salami slices
Cheese slices

METHOD
Mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add in the egg and soft butter, mix everything well and let the dough rise for about 2 hours.
Roll out the dough cut into strips, top with salami and cheese.
Wrap them and spread with egg yolk. Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 40 minutes.

node.text:
The whole family will love this buns for dinner! 
 
INGREDIENTS
250ml (1 cup) warm milk
1 large egg
50g (1/4 cup) yogurt
50g (1/4 cup) sugar
400g (3 1/4 cup) flour
7g dry yeast
4g (1 tsp) salt
60g (1/4 cup) butter
Butter for filling
 
Egg wash:
1 egg
20ml (2 tbsp) milk
Salt
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl, add warm milk, egg, and sugar. Mix well. Add flour, yeast, and salt. Mix. Rest for 20 minutes.
Add the butter and mix. Knead and fold the dough until smooth. When it's smooth, place in an oiled bowl and rest for 60 minutes.
Deflate the dough by punching out the gas. Flatten out the dough and divide it into 16 pieces. Round each into a ball. Rest for 20 minutes.
Flatten the dough upside down. Fill with butter. Pinch the seams to seal.
Place in a greased baking dish. Cover for 20 minutes.
Brush with egg wash. Top with salt.
Bake at 360F/180C for 18-20 minutes. Brush with melted butter. Serve.

node.text:
These savory #croissants are a must-try! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Dough:
500g flour
70g melted butter
7g dry yeast
10g salt
40g sugar
300ml milk
 
Filling:
Salami
Mozzarella cheese
 
Coat:
Sesame seeds
Egg
Milk

METHOD
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add the yeast to warm milk, then pour over the flour. Add melted butter and mix very well.
Let rise for 4 hours.
Cut the dough into two large pieces. Roll out one piece into a circle, then cut into 8 even triangle slices. Place salami and cheese on each piece. Roll from the largest edge to form a croissant.
Place them on a baking sheet and rest for 1 hour.
Mix egg and milk and cover each croissant. Sprinkle sesame seeds on each one. Bake for 20 minutes at 225°C (437 °F).

node.text:
These #appetizer ideas are brilliant!

1) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
200g cream cheese
Pistachio
Cling film

METHOD
Spread cream cheese on a slice of mortadella. Roll up and cut into medium pieces.
Sprinkle with pistachio grains.
-----------------------------------------
2) Ham
INGREDIENTS
Sliced Large bread
Rocket salad
Mayonnaise
Ham
Cling film
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten. Spread mayonnaise all over the slice, add ham and rocket salad.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread mayonnaise on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut in pieces.
-----------------------------------------
3) Salmon
INGREDIENTS
Sliced large bread
Salmon
Salad
Cream cheese
Cling film
Chives
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten.
Mix cream cheese with chives and spread over the entire slice. Add salmon and salad to the entire slice of bread.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread cream cheese on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut into slices.
-----------------------------------------
4) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
Ricotta
Pistachio
Bread
Oil
Honey

METHOD
Cut several slices of bread.
Place them in a pan until toasted.
Mix ricotta with oil and cover each bread.
Add pistachio grains, slices of mortadella, honey and more pistachios to each slice.

node.title: 4 simple and delicious appetizers to surprise everyone!

node.text:
Easy and delicious, this #zucchini roll is perfect for dinner!

INGREDIENTS
1 zucchini
4 eggs
100g (½ cup) cheese
Salt
Pepper

METHOD
Grate the zucchini. Drain the water.
Beat eggs, salt, and pepper in a mixing bowl. Add zucchini and grated cheese. Mix.
Fry the mixture in an oiled pan, slowly roll it out, and gradually add.
Cut it into pieces and serve.

node.text:
Have you ever tried to add instant coffee to your #pancakes? The result is delicious! 

INGREDIENTS
3 bananas
1 tbsp instant coffee
2 eggs
300ml milk
250g flour
10g baking powder
3 tbsp sugar
Hazelnut grains
Hazelnut cream
 
METHOD
Cut the bananas in a bowl, add instant coffee, eggs and blend very well. Add milk, flour, baking powder, sugar, and mix well.
Cook in a pan for 5 minutes on both sides.
Spread hazelnut cream on each pancake and serve with hazelnut grains.

node.text:
Ready in a few minutes, this #bread is super delicious! 
 
INGREDIENTS
900g (7 cups) flour
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm milk
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm water
4g (1 tsp) salt
7g dry yeast
Olive oil
Parsley

METHOD
Add flour, yeast, water, milk, and salt to the mixing bowl. Knead the dough. Leave to rest for 60 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 parts and roll out with a rolling pin.
Bake on high heat in a pan. Coat with oil and parsley. Serve.

These #calzones are delicious, you won't be able to stop at one! 
 
INGREDIENTS
600g (5 cups) flour
330ml (1 ¼ cups) water
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
25ml (2 tbsp) olive oil
 
Filling:
100ml (2/5 cup) tomato pasta
100g mozzarella
100g ham
100g (2/5 cup) bechamel

METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the flour, yeast, and a little water at a time, then add the salt and oil and start kneading.
Knead everything well until it forms a smooth and soft dough, then with a rolling pin roll out a sheet of about 5mm high.
With a pasta bowl, make lots of circles, stuffed with tomato and mozzarella or béchamel and cooked ham.
Then close all the panzerotti in the shape of a half-moon and seal with a fork so that the filling does not come out during cooking.
Now fry them in abundant hot oil for a couple of minutes on each side or until you see them golden. Serve.

The two-color cake is DIVINE! Everyone will ask you the recipe!

INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
60g (1/3 cup) sugar
4g (1 tsp) vanilla sugar
60ml (¼ cup) oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
250g (2 cups) flour
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
10g (1 tbsp) cocoa powder
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil, and milk. Mix. Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour 80% of the mixture into a baking tin.
Mix the rest of the mixture with cocoa and make tufts on the cake.
Bake at 360°F / 180°C for 25 minutes. Garnish with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
You have never tried an #omelet this tasty!

INGREDIENTS
Red bell pepper
Yellow bell pepper
6 eggs
50g parmesan
Chives
Garlic
Thyme
Extra virgin olive oil
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
Add minced garlic and oil to a pan. Sprinkle over dried thyme. Cut the peppers, add to the pan, and cook. Then add chives
Pour 6 eggs into a bowl, add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly
Add the pepper mixture to the bowl with the egg and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a pan and cook on both sides to get an omelet.

This #chocolatepudding is so creamy and irresistible!

INGREDIENTS
1l (4 cups) milk
2 egg yolks
1 cup flour
1 cup sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 tbsp butter
1 tsp vanilla sugar
1/2 cup chocolate
240ml (1 cup) water
Biscuits
 
METHOD
Into the pan add egg yolks, flour, cocoa powder, sugar, and milk, cook on low heat until thick. Add in butter, chocolate, and vanilla extract. Turn off the heat and pour in water.
Layout biscuits on the bottom of each plate. Cover them with prepared chocolate mixture, and repeat it again. Refrigerate for 1 hour, sprinkle with more chocolate chips.

node.text:
Just eggs, veggies and a muffin pan to make an incredible dinner! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
Butter
1 onion
Garlic
Carrots
Red pepper
Leeks
4 eggs
80ml (1/3 cup) milk
Parmesan
Salt
Black pepper
Extra virgin olive oil
 
METHOD
Melt the butter in a frying pan. Then add grated garlic, carrot, onion, red pepper, leek, salt, pepper, and mix. Put in a bowl once cooked.
Mix the eggs and milk in a bowl, add salt and pepper, then add the cooked vegetables and mix well.
Brush some oil over the muffin tray then pour in the egg mixture. Cook for 15 minutes at 200ºC (392ºF).

node.text:
This idea is so cute, perfect to surprise everyone with a few basic ingredients! 

INGREDIENTS
320g (2.5 cups) flour
3 tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp salt
7g dry yeast
190ml (3/4 cup) warm milk
1 egg
1 egg yolk
3 tbsp soft butter
Salami slices
Cheese slices

METHOD
Mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add in the egg and soft butter, mix everything well and let the dough rise for about 2 hours.
Roll out the dough cut into strips, top with salami and cheese.
Wrap them and spread with egg yolk. Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 40 minutes.

node.text:
NOW you can make pancakes without a scale! You only need a tablespoon 🤩🤩

INGREDIENTS
1 egg
250ml (1 cup) of milk
2 tbsp oil
4 tbsp of flour
1 tbsp of sugar
1 tsp of baking powder
 
METHOD
Add egg yolks and sugar to the mixing bowl. Whisk with a mixer.
Add milk, oil, and sifted flour. Mix.
In another bowl, whisk the egg whites.
Mix with the first mixture and add the baking powder. Rest for 5 minutes.
Bake in a pan. Drizzle with maple syrup and serve.

Have you ever tried potato in this way? 

Have you ever tried potatoes in this way? 
3 Potatoes
Bacon
Cheese
Pecorino cheese
Olive oil
 
METHOD
Add potatoes to water and cook for 3-4 minutes.
Take the skewer sticks and place them in front and on the back of the potatoes. Cut the potatoes from the top to a thickness of 4-5 millimeters.
Add the cheese and the bacon to the cavity of the potatoes.
Sprinkle the potatoes with the pecorino cheese and oil and bake at 356°F/180°C for 20 minutes.

node.text:
The whole family will love this buns for dinner! 
 
INGREDIENTS
250ml (1 cup) warm milk
1 large egg
50g (1/4 cup) yogurt
50g (1/4 cup) sugar
400g (3 1/4 cup) flour
7g dry yeast
4g (1 tsp) salt
60g (1/4 cup) butter
Butter for filling
 
Egg wash:
1 egg
20ml (2 tbsp) milk
Salt
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl, add warm milk, egg, and sugar. Mix well. Add flour, yeast, and salt. Mix. Rest for 20 minutes.
Add the butter and mix. Knead and fold the dough until smooth. When it's smooth, place in an oiled bowl and rest for 60 minutes.
Deflate the dough by punching out the gas. Flatten out the dough and divide it into 16 pieces. Round each into a ball. Rest for 20 minutes.
Flatten the dough upside down. Fill with butter. Pinch the seams to seal.
Place in a greased baking dish. Cover for 20 minutes.
Brush with egg wash. Top with salt.
Bake at 360F/180C for 18-20 minutes. Brush with melted butter. Serve.

node.text:
These savory #croissants are a must-try! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Dough:
500g flour
70g melted butter
7g dry yeast
10g salt
40g sugar
300ml milk
 
Filling:
Salami
Mozzarella cheese
 
Coat:
Sesame seeds
Egg
Milk

METHOD
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add the yeast to warm milk, then pour over the flour. Add melted butter and mix very well.
Let rise for 4 hours.
Cut the dough into two large pieces. Roll out one piece into a circle, then cut into 8 even triangle slices. Place salami and cheese on each piece. Roll from the largest edge to form a croissant.
Place them on a baking sheet and rest for 1 hour.
Mix egg and milk and cover each croissant. Sprinkle sesame seeds on each one. Bake for 20 minutes at 225°C (437 °F).
